properties.Name: East Malvern Path/Shimmy to Dandenong Creek Trail
Johnson St & Studley Park Rd
properties.description: Avoid as mostly not bike friendly but may be your only option for some east-west trips

properties.Name: Kenilworth Pde, Norman St, Studley Rd
High St
properties.description: Activity street which is can be ridden with caution when necessary but alternatives are better where feasible

properties.Name: Gertrude St & Langridge St
properties.description: Narrow bike lane with tram tracks alongside. Use caution

properties.Name: Church St & Chapel St
properties.description: Avoid where possible as is busy shopping street with high dooring risk. Can be only option for some north-south travel

properties.Name: Westbourne Grove
properties.description: Steep hill going east!

properties.Name: Sydney Rd
properties.description: Major dooring risk outside of clearway times so ride at least 1m from doors and carefully

properties.Name: Dean St to Moonee Ponds Creek Trail
Elizabeth St
properties.description: Tram super stops mean this busy street is now often inefficient for bikes (no filtering). Need to be very aware

properties.Name: Macaulay Rd & Kensington Rd
properties.description: Big hill so use Bellair, Ormond, Childers if possible

properties.Name: William Barak Bridge
properties.description: Bridge across rail tracks and busy roads connecting city to MCG

properties.Name: Dalton Rd Bike Offroad Path
properties.description: - Runs along western side of Dalton Rd. Is 2-way

properties.Name: Fraser St, Cramer St, Shaftsbury St
Clarke St shortcut
properties.description: Less steep going east than Westbourne St

properties.Name: South Morang Line Shimmy
properties.description: Back streets connected route

properties.Name: CCT Wayfinder - Footscray Rd crossover
properties.description: The CCT turns 90 degrees east here - you have to cross Footscray Rd to pick it up again

properties.Name: AAMI Park Path
properties.description: The best shortcut from Swan St to the Morell Bridge and Botanic Gardens

properties.Name: O'Hea St Copenhagen Lanes
properties.description: Separated lanes cover most of the way between Derby St and Stockade Ave

properties.Name: MCG - Swan St Cycle Bridge
properties.description: The best shortcut across busy Brunton Ave and the railway lines.

properties.Name: Footscray Rd to Capital City Trail
Collins St
properties.description: High dooring risk in some sections. But is often only practical east-west route through city

properties.Name: Dryburgh St to La Trobe St
Brunswick East Shimmy Route (Amess, John, Ellesbury)
properties.description: Local streets north-south route

properties.Name: Flemington Rd
properties.description: Often is the only practical bike route here but has narrow bike lanes with some dooring risk

properties.Name: Capital City Trail to Heyington Bridge
Westbury St & The Avenue
properties.description: Note: Have to use pedestrian crossing at Dandenong Road, and it sometimes takes a while.

properties.Name: Elster Creek / Elwood Canal Shared Path
Smith St
properties.description: High dooring risk

properties.Name: Nepean Hwy Separated Path
properties.description: If you are heading SE away from the city along Nepean Hwy, best to use this path on the other side of the road, rather than going in and out of services lanes, as you have to merge with the traffic too often.

properties.Name: Caribbean Market to Upper Ferntree Gully Path
Scotchmans Creek to Blind Creek Shimmy
Exhibition St
properties.description: Peak hour bike lanes exist apart from between Little Bourke St to Little Collins St

properties.Name: Spencer St
properties.description: Is often only practical north-south route here but is busy, no continuous bike lane and has dooring risk

properties.Name: Spring St north to La Trobe
Hopetoun Bridge
properties.description: Avoid. Bikes use footpath but its narrow and there are many fast-moving trucks close by.

properties.Name: Carlton Gardens east-west route
properties.description:
- Informal shared space for riding east-west. Give way to pedestrians!
- Not an official bike route so watch out for the occasional "blitz" of cycling fines in Carlton Gardens

properties.Name: Bellair St, Ormond St, Childers St
Sages Rd to Metropolitan Ring Rd via Hume Hwy
properties.description:
- During non-clearway hours the left lane of Hume Hwy has space next to parked cars
- During clearway hours use footpath

properties.Name: Blackshaws Rd to Clelland Rd (Kororoit link)
properties.description: - Only direct connecting link for Kororoit Trail. Need to use footpath and either busy road or dirt shoulder

properties.Name: Grattan St
properties.description:
- Mostly wide enough to be safe but no lengthy bike lanes so other routes preferable
- Safe shared path outside Uni of Melb

properties.Name: Swanston St - North
properties.description: Near College Crescent use shared path to cross over to Cemetary shared path

properties.Name: Queens Parade
properties.description: Mostly bike lanes on both sides but has some missing sections you can see in Google Maps Cycling layer

properties.Name: Webb bridge, Munro St to Sandridge Trail
